{"id":"pattern-example-001","type":"pattern","fact":"Example: Use mock factories for all test data instead of manual mock objects with 'as Type' assertions.","recommendation":"Create centralized mock factory functions (createMockUser, createMockOrg, etc.) and import them in tests.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"documentation","reference":"Testing guide","date":"2026-01-09"}],"tags":["testing","mocks","factories"],"affectedFiles":["**/*.test.ts"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-01-09T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-non-recursive-dsl-type-for-bounded-nesting","type":"pattern","fact":"For filter DSL types that allow exactly N levels of nesting, use a structurally bounded type rather than a recursive type + runtime depth guard. Pattern: outer tree holds Vec<ItemEnum> where ItemEnum = Leaf(T) | Group(InnerGroup), and InnerGroup holds Vec<T> (not Vec<ItemEnum>). Depth > N is compile-time impossible — no validator code path to forget.","recommendation":"Prefer ConditionGroup::All(Vec<Condition>) over ConditionItem::Group(Box<ConditionTree>) when the spec says 'one level of nesting'. The non-recursive form is simpler, has no ts-rs circular import risk, and makes leaves_dfs() a two-level flat_map instead of a recursive DFS.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"plan review gate iteration 5 scope reviewer finding + B-W1 implementation 2026-06-08","date":"2026-06-08"}],"tags":["xvision-filters","DSL","type-design","nesting","serde","Rust"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-filters/src/**/*.rs"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
{"id":"pattern-explicit-accessor-methods-over-ambiguous-shims","type":"pattern","fact":"When a public method's semantics become ambiguous after a type change (e.g. conditions() returning &[Condition] from Vec<ConditionItem> — does it return top-level items? all leaves? DFS?), removing it and replacing with purpose-specific methods is worth the 8+ call-site updates. Each callsite states its intent: items() for top-level, leaves_dfs() for all leaves, leaf_count() for sizing.","recommendation":"When evolving a container type (Vec<Condition> → Vec<ConditionItem>), audit every callsite of the old accessor and determine what semantics it actually needed. Then introduce separate methods with unambiguous names. The short-term pain of migration is offset by eliminating future ambiguity bugs.","confidence":"high","provenance":[{"source":"agent","reference":"B-W1 conditions() removal 2026-06-08 — 8 call sites in 5 files + 2 test files migrated","date":"2026-06-08"}],"tags":["xvision-filters","API-design","refactoring","Rust","ConditionTree"],"affectedFiles":["crates/xvision-filters/src/**/*.rs","crates/xvision-engine/src/autooptimizer/mutator.rs"],"affectedServices":[],"createdAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","updatedAt":"2026-06-08T00:00:00Z","usageCount":0,"helpfulCount":0,"outdatedReports":0}
